<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTER ROLLER TYPE - REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="4">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <para>Remove the following prior to servicing the valve train, camshaft, cam followers and push rods. Refer to
            the appropriate manual section.
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Injection Lines</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Injection Pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Intake Manifold</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Valley Pan and Gasket Assembly</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Injection Pump Gear</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Water Pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Front Plate</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Valve Covers</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Valve Lever Assembly</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Engine Mounted Fuel Supply Pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel Filter Assembly</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <figure id="ef4350402" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg11079" filename="../figcg1/CG11079.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4.2 Hydraulic Valve Lifter</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the valve lifter guide retainer (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350403">4.3</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ), by removing the three bolts and washers which fasten it to the block.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove valve lifter guides (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350404">4.4</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove hydraulic valve lifters (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350405">4.5</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>IDENTIFY HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTER POSITION AS TO CYLINDER HEAD AND PORT IN ENGINE BLOCK AS WELL
                        AS DIRECTION OF ROTATION SO THEY CAN BE REINSTALLED IN THEIR ORIGINAL POSITION.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>As a general rule, hydraulic valve lifters should be left alone when they are functioning
                        satisfactorily and the valve train remains quiet.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350403" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11080" filename="../figcg1/CG11080.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.3 Valve Lifter Guide Retainer Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350404" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11081" filename="../figcg1/CG11081.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.4 Valve Lifter Guide Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350405" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11082" filename="../figcg1/CG11082.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.5 Valve Lifter Removal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
